The paper discusses methods for approximating pairwise and columnwise commute times and Katz scores using matrix computations and numerical linear algebra techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). However, given the focus on matrix computations and numerical linear algebra, cs.NA is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.DS and cs.SI. The paper also discusses the use of personalized PageRank algorithms, which could potentially place it in the cs.LG sub-category, while the focus on control and optimization could place it in the cs.SY sub-category.
